abstract: Campaigning officially ended on Thursday for Iran's parliamentary election, a day before a vote seen as a litmus test of the popularity of the clerical establishment.
snippet: Campaigning officially ended on Thursday for Iran's parliamentary election, a day before a vote seen as a litmus test of the popularity of the clerical establishment.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — Campaigning officially ended on Thursday for Iran's parliamentary election, a day before a vote seen as a litmus test of the popularity of the clerical establishment.
headline_main: Iran Prepares for Vote Seen as Litmus Test for Establishment
headline_print_headline: Iran Prepares for Vote Seen as Litmus Test for Establishment

abstract: Making his debut onstage, he was greeted by forceful challenges from Elizabeth Warren and the rest of the Democratic field.
snippet: Making his debut onstage, he was greeted by forceful challenges from Elizabeth Warren and the rest of the Democratic field.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg bobbed behind his lectern, as if the motion might deliver him somewhere more comfortable. He blinked, then blinked some more. He appeared unsteady — for all the preparation his billions might buy him — on questions of race and gender that could not have come as a surprise.

abstract: Defense Secretary Mark Esper used his first-ever visit to a nuclear missile field in frigid North Dakota to tout the Trump administration's multibillion-dollar plan for a top-to-bottom modernization of the nuclear arsenal. The costly project is necessary, he said, to keep up with Russia and outpace China.
snippet: Defense Secretary Mark Esper used his first-ever visit to a nuclear missile field in frigid North Dakota to tout the Trump administration's multibillion-dollar plan for a top-to-bottom modernization of the nuclear arsenal. The costly project is ne...
lead_paragraph: MINOT AIR FORCE BASE, N.D. — Defense Secretary Mark Esper used his first-ever visit to a nuclear missile field in frigid North Dakota to tout the Trump administration's multibillion-dollar plan for a top-to-bottom modernization of the nuclear arsenal. The costly project is necessary, he said, to keep up with Russia and outpace China.
headline_main: Pentagon Chief Visits Nuke Base to Highlight Weapon Spending

headline_main: Hanau, Coronavirus, Michael Bloomberg: Your Thursday Briefing

abstract: A slowdown in U.S. growth last year was at least partly the fault of President Donald Trump's global trade battles and the resulting hit to business investment, the administration's top economist said on Thursday in an outlook for the coming years.
snippet: A slowdown in U.S. growth last year was at least partly the fault of President Donald Trump's global trade battles and the resulting hit to business investment, the administration's top economist said on Thursday in an outlook for the coming years...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A slowdown in U.S. growth last year was at least partly the fault of President Donald Trump's global trade battles and the resulting hit to business investment, the administration's top economist said on Thursday in an outlook for the coming years.
headline_main: Trump Economist Says 'Uncertainty' From Trade Disputes Hit Business Investment
headline_print_headline: Trump Economist Says 'Uncertainty' From Trade Disputes Hit Business Investment

abstract: The latest Economic Report of the President remains optimistic about growth while clashing with Democrats who have proposed breaking up large companies to improve competition.
snippet: The latest Economic Report of the President remains optimistic about growth while clashing with Democrats who have proposed breaking up large companies to improve competition.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and his economic team see “no need to hastily rewrite the federal government’s antitrust rules,” drawing a battle line with leading Democratic presidential candidates on an issue that has increasingly drawn the attention of economists, legal scholars and other academics.

headline_main: Trump Administration Sees No Threat to Economy From Monopolies
headline_print_headline: Looking at Antitrust Rules, the Administration Says Big Is Beautiful

abstract: The president has reveled in the declines in Americans receiving aid from several government programs in recent years, citing his economic policies as a catalyst.
snippet: The president has reveled in the declines in Americans receiving aid from several government programs in recent years, citing his economic policies as a catalyst.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump likes to claim credit for the number of Americans who have stopped receiving food stamps since he entered office. In July 2018, he said 3.5 million had fallen from the rolls; the next spring, five million had. In his State of the Union speech this month, the number had grown to seven million.
